The paper focuses on Educational Data Mining and social interaction in learning, which suggests a strong connection to the category of "Computers and Society" (cs.CY). The use of behavior modeling and intervention for support suggests a connection to "Machine Learning" (cs.LG) and "Computation and Language" (cs.CL). The discussion of a social recommender system suggests a connection to "Human-Computer Interaction" (cs.HC) and "Information Retrieval" (cs.IR).
